name: Enforce TypeScript and type safety
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: JavaScript files, 'any' types, or missing type annotations
then: Use TypeScript (.tsx) with proper interfaces from types/api.ts
why: Type safety prevents runtime errors and ensures data integrity in enterprise applications.
description: All React components must use TypeScript with proper type definitions. Import interfaces from centralized types/api.ts. Never use 'any' type or duplicate type definitions locally.
shortDescription: Use TypeScript with centralized types, no 'any' types
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.tsx", "frontend/src/**/*.ts"]

---
name: Use centralized API hooks for all data operations
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: Direct fetch() calls or local API state management
then: Use centralized hooks like useFunds(), useCreateFund(), useEntities()
why: Centralized API integration provides consistent error handling, loading states, and reduces code duplication across teams.
description: All API calls must go through centralized hooks that provide consistent error handling, loading states, and data management patterns.
shortDescription: Use centralized API hooks, no direct fetch calls
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Handle form data type conversion properly
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Form data used directly without type conversion
then: Convert string form data to proper types (e.g., FundType enum, numbers)
why: Form data comes as strings but API expects typed enums and numbers. Prevents data corruption and runtime errors.
description: Form inputs return strings, but APIs expect typed data. Always convert form values to proper types before API calls.
shortDescription: Convert form strings to proper types
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Implement error boundaries and user-friendly error handling
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Components without error handling for API failures
then: Add error states with user-friendly messages using Alert component
why: Graceful error handling is crucial for enterprise user experience and prevents app crashes.
description: All async operations must have proper error handling with user-friendly messages. Use error boundaries to catch and display errors gracefully.
shortDescription: Handle errors gracefully with user-friendly messages
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]
